original_result.user_prompt: What's VT100 code to render green terminal text?
original_result.completion_text:
The VT100 code to render green terminal text uses the ANSI escape sequence for setting the foreground color to green. In this case, the code is "\033[32m". You can wrap your desired text within this code to display it in green. For instance:

```
\033[32mThis text will appear in green.\033[0m
```

The `\033` represents the escape character, `[32]` specifies the color green, and `\033[0m` resets the console color back to default after displaying the colored text.
